{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"33b8149a-34a1-424b-95cc-fa06ca4857dc","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. I can help you analyze it — here's what you'll need to do:\n\n### Analyzing a .NET Crash Dump\n\n**1. Upload the dump file** to this session so I can work with it, or analyze it locally using:\n\n**2. `dotnet-dump analyze`** (recommended, cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\nThen inside the interactive session, run:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all managed threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n**3. On Windows**, you can also use **WinDbg** with the SOS debugging extension.\n\n---\n\n**If you can share the dump file here**, I'll run `dotnet-dump analyze` for you and investigate the crash. Would you like to upload it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5fa922eb-0742-42c3-9897-7c17fe49c5fd","outputTokens":257,"requestId":"D808:14859A:3523FA8:3A2F927:69FBF17A"},"id":"fabd01d9-1024-4f01-9f13-cc3b77d90520","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:57:21.740Z","parentId":"26e4411b-ddc4-408e-a79a-355a485f50c7"}
